Scientists detected the complex organic molecules in a disk of gas and dust around a star 455 light years away where planets are likely to be forming . 
  Discovery is a boost for finding alien organisms and suggests the conditions that spawned life on Earth are not unique to our solar system . 
  Radio telescope observations showed the disk surrounding the million-year-old star MWC 480 to be 'brimming' with methyl cyanide . 
 